commit.message: Fix up Ruby 3.0.* tests based on updated default method sorting
When sorting methods, only sort by time if the difference is greater than 0.0001 seconds. This helps make test results more consistent.
Remove test gems used to debug a crash
Define rb_class_attached_object for older versions of Ruby.
Fix #326. Crash was caused by rp_methods holding a reference to Profile ruby objects which were moved during GC compaction phase.
Run merge_test.rb on Ruby 3.1 and higher
Try with scheduler from ruby 3.2.1 (the version from 3.0.3 does not work with ruby 3.2.1).
Turn on allow_exceptions to determine what is happening with the merge_test.rb on Ruby 3.0
Fix broken ruby-prof cli. Also make options alphabetical. Fixes #323.
